    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Curacao</placeName>
                <date>11th Septr. 1852</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I last had this pleasure on<lb/> the <date>27th</date> Ulto: since
                then I have received yours under date<lb/>
                <date>2nd Augt.</date> together with the “Occidents” of that month, and<lb/> the
                nine numbers of <date>Augt.</date> &amp; <date>Septe. 1851</date>, these have
                arrived<lb/> at a good time to enable me to make the collections for<lb/> the same.
                I have shown the page of your Bible to<lb/> several of our Members, all like the
                print <add>ר.פי.פ</add>. I have<lb/> therefore to request of you to send me a few
                extra copies<lb/> to those subscribed for in your prospectus, as I am sure<lb/> to
                dispose of them, I would recommend a few unbound<lb/> and a few bound neatly. I am
                in hopes of soon giving<lb/> you a more favorable report of our subscribers for
                your<lb/> Periodical, and shall use my efforts to influence our<lb/> People to
                promote your labours.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have noticed your remarks relative to your prayer<lb/> books, and
                shall in conformity execute your wishes, as<lb/> soon as a favorable opportunity
                offers itself, this vessel<lb/> leaves this for <add>?</add>oro under charter, which
                prevents me from<lb/> fulfilling your order now. I shall try all in my<lb/> power to
                procure and forward you the Citiora &amp; Lulabion<add>?</add><lb/> as soon as
                possible, the Brig “Abrue”<add>?</add> is expected here</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>in a few days, by her I hope to be able to send them.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My brother in Law <persName>Nathan</persName> tenders you his
                best<lb/> wishes, and joins me with my family Circle in wishing<lb/> you many happy
                returns of our approaching Holy days,<lb/> with best wishes for your health &amp;
                happiness.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am very truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Moses Lindo</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
